22%3Cp%3EThe%20festival%20of%20Eid%20evokes%20nostalgia.%20School%20days%20were%20reminiscent%20of%20gathering%20around%20the%20table%20with%20my%20friends%2C%20waiting%20for%20the%20feast%20that%20would%20follow%20the%20fast%20during%20Ramadan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20table%20creaking%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345758%2Fbest-places-for-ramzan-food-in-bengaluru-iftar-ramadan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eiftar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(the%20fast-breaking%20evening%20meal)%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20signal%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%E2%80%99s%20fast.%20Hours%20of%20abstaining%20from%20food%20and%20drink%20would%20make%20my%20friends%20hungry%20enough%20to%20devour%20everything%20in%20front%20of%20them%2C%20I%20would%20think.%20But%20I%E2%80%99d%20watch%20in%20awe%20as%20they%20elegantly%20took%20some%20%3Cem%3Ekhajoor%3C%2Fem%3E%20(dates)%2C%20followed%20by%20fresh%20fruits%20and%20then%20meaty%20snacks%2C%20and%20the%20likes.%20The%20%3Cem%3Eiftar%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%20then%20be%20washed%20down%20with%20a%20drink%20of%20%3Cem%3Eroohafza%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20refreshing%20drink%20made%20with%20basil%20seeds%2C%20fruits%2C%20herbs%20and%20flowers).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20among%20many%20other%20delicacies%20set%20before%20us%2C%20one%20dish%20reigned%20supreme%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eseviyan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20vermicelli%20pudding%20made%20with%20ghee%2C%20rice%20vermicelli%20noodles%2C%20milk%2C%20spices%2C%20and%20a%20sweetener.%20While%20it%20is%20a%20common%20guest%20at%20the%3Cem%3E%20iftar%3C%2Fem%3E%20feast%2C%20my%20friend%20Thousif%20Raza%20explains%20it%20is%20its%20fancier%20cousin%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esheer%20khurma%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20makes%20an%20appearance%20on%20Eid.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESheer%20khurma%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20made%20with%20extra%20%3Cem%3Ekhoya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(thickened%20milk)%20and%20dry%20fruits%20%E2%80%94%20a%20richer%20version%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20nevertheless%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F247633%2Fla-kheer-deli-shivang-sood-pune-startup-kheer-indian-traditional-dessert-homemade-recipes-success-story-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreamy%20concoctions%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20fit%20for%20kings.%20Once%20prepared%20for%20royalty%2C%20the%20dish%20reflects%20regional%20sensibilities%2C%20with%20each%20diaspora%20adding%20to%20it%20what%20they%20deem%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20the%20vermicelli%2C%20one%20of%20the%20main%20ingredients%20in%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20are%20hidden%20by%20the%20passage%20of%20time.%20Translating%20to%20%E2%80%98little%20worms%E2%80%99%2C%20these%20thin%20rice%20noodles%20have%20been%20a%20part%20of%20diets%20as%20far%20back%20as%20the%201660s.%20And%2C%20each%20cuisine%20has%20embraced%20a%20different%20form%20of%20it%20in%20its%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20706px)%20100vw%2C%20706px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22706%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seviyan%20is%20a%20milk-based%20delicacy%20that%20is%20often%20prepared%20around%20Eid%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287.jpg%20706w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287-298x300.jpg%20298w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287-500x504.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287-150x151.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190421-1712583287-96x96.jpg%2096w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346835%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESeviyan%20is%20a%20milk-based%20delicacy%20that%20is%20often%20prepared%20around%20Eid%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Instagram%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCSeuRQ_Fn9O%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAround.Alba%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAn%20ironic%20coloured%20history%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeutral%20shades%20with%20hints%20of%20yellow%20is%20how%20a%20culinary%20aficionado%20would%20describe%20the%20vermicelli.%20In%20Italy%2C%20the%20vermicelli%20features%20in%20both%20sweet%20and%20savoury%20dishes.%20When%20mixed%20with%20tomatoes%2C%20garlic%20and%20anchovies%2C%20it%20makes%20for%20great%20spaghetti%2C%20while%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F308752%2Fdodha-barfi-history-story-of-wrestler-harbans-vig-tales-of-taste-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14th-century%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlighted%20how%20it%20blended%20well%20with%20wheat%20flour%2C%20almonds%2C%20eggs%20and%20sugar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201770%20American%20cookbook%20%E2%80%98The%20Art%20of%20Cookery%E2%80%99%20spoke%20of%20how%20the%20vermicelli%20made%20an%20excellent%20meal%20when%20blended%20well%20with%20egg%20yolks%20and%20flour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsian%20cuisine%20embraced%20vermicelli%20and%20its%20many%20forms%20right%20since%20the%20Qin%20dynasty%20dating%20back%20to%20221%20BCE%3B%20whether%20as%20%3Cem%3Emi%20fen%3C%2Fem%3E%20(rice%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emung%20bean%20vermicelli%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cellophane%20or%20glass%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emisua%3C%2Fem%3E%20(wheat-based%20vermicelli).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20Indian%20variations%20of%20vermicelli%2C%20local%20lore%20tells%20us%20that%20the%20only%20way%20perhaps%20that%20vermicelli%20made%20its%20way%20into%20the%20subcontinent%20is%20through%20trade%20networks%20extending%20between%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20Egypt%2C%20the%20technique%20of%20frying%20vermicelli%20(%3Cem%3Eshe%E2%80%99reya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20butter%20or%20oil%20was%20prevalent.%20Once%20fried%2C%20water%20would%20be%20added%20to%20the%20fried%20noodles%20and%20it%20would%20be%20cooked%20with%20rice.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261268%2Fbiryani-map-of-india-taste-the-history-find-your-favourite-among-28-versions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20hearty%20meal%3C%2Fa%3E!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20article%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0explores%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20sweet%20dish.%20Hand%20rolling%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20was%20once%20a%20traditional%20occupation%2C%20gained%20popularity%20during%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Mughal%20rule.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20said%20that%20Emperor%20Humayun%20ignited%20the%20love%20for%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20court%20by%20reintroducing%20the%20Persian%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekurma%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edum%20ki%20seviyan.%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%2C%20it%20was%C2%A0Emperor%20Shah%20Jahan%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20dish%20becoming%20its%20current%20version%20with%20spices%2C%20ghee%20and%20dry%20fruits.%20An%20anecdote%20often%20told%20is%20how%20the%20Emperor%20requested%20a%20special%20sunset-coloured%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evarq%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(an%20edible%20foil%20garnishing)%20to%20accompany%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20tradition%20lasted%20until%20the%20time%20of%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20who%20would%20prepare%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20ingredient%20entered%20India%2C%20it%20was%20local%20palate%20preferences%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20many%20vermicelli-based%20dishes%20that%20now%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Oxford%20Companion%20to%20Food%E2%80%99%20by%20Alan%20Davidson%20and%20Tom%20Jaine%2C%20says%20the%20following%20about%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20The%20Sanskrit%20name%20for%20noodles%20is%20%3Cem%3Esevika%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20may%20derive%20from%20an%20unrecorded%20word%20meaning%20thread%20connected%20with%20the%20root%20%3Cem%3Esiv%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20sewing.%20%3Cem%3ESev%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20crisp%20fried%20noodles%20prepared%20from%20%3Cem%3Ebesan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea)%20flour.%20%3Cem%3ESeviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20%3Cem%3Eseviya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Esivayya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eshavayi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20usually%20refers%20to%20a%20sweet%20dish%20of%20vermicelli%20noodles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20637px)%20100vw%2C%20637px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20sheer%20khurma%20is%20a%20premium%20variety%20of%20seviyan%20prepared%20with%20khoya%20and%20dry%20fruits%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593.jpg%20637w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-270x300.jpg%20270w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-500x557.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-150x167.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346837%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20cla