.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-03-06-at-10.04.59-PM-2-1710505101-768x604.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-03-06-at-10.04.59-PM-2-1710505101-150x118.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344976%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22835%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20range%20of%20dishes%20served%20at%20the%20Swadhin%20Bharat%20Hindu%20Hotel%20includes%20fish%2C%20mutton%20and%20vegetable%20delicacies%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Arunangshu%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20legacy%20of%20pice%20hotels%20in%20Kolkata%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20among%20political%20circles%2C%20%3Cem%3Epice%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehotels%20were%20loved%20by%20even%20the%20working%20class.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20name%20%E2%80%98pice%E2%80%99%20borrows%20from%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98paisa%E2%80%99%20considered%20the%20lowest%20denomination%20in%20Indian%20currency.%20The%20%3Cem%3Epice%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20a%20monetary%20unit%20of%20British%20India%20equivalent%20to%20one-quarter%20of%20an%20anna.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261622%2Fwhats-bitter-beloved-of-bengalis-shukto-a-culinary-gem-with-a-story-to-tell%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20light%20on%20the%20pocket%2C%20an%20advantage%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20Independence%20movement%20as%20Indians%20struggled%20with%20migrations%2C%20loss%20of%20business%2C%20and%20limited%20food%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20food%20historian%20Tanushree%20Bhowmik%20emphasised%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EPice%3C%2Fem%3E%20hotels%20stand%20out%20as%20the%20first%20commercial%20indigenous%20eating%20places%20in%20the%20city.%20People%20moved%20from%20rural%20to%20urban%20areas%20as%20the%20economy%20shifted%